From: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Feb 2017 19:50:33 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1741/2066] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-x: Disable SCIF1
 RTS/CTS hardware flow control by default

This patch disables ths RTS/CTS hardware flow control to compensate for
the default DeviceTree of Salvator-X board on R8A7796 SoC.

Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts |    1 -
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
index f8595c6..9d4946fe 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
@@ -613,7 +613,6 @@
 	pinctrl-0 = <&scif1_pins>;
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
 
-	uart-has-rtscts;
 	/* Please use exclusively to the hscif1 node */
 	status = "okay";
 };
